function.name: match_history_for_dota_2_steam_web
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "dota_2_steam_web", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "will return the latest 25 public matches in JSON format. You can request it in XML format"

function.name: match_details_for_dota_2_steam_web
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "dota_2_steam_web", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "To retrieve the specific details of a match, use this API:"

matches_requested.description: Defaults is 25 matches, this can limit to less

date_min.description: date in UTC seconds since Jan 1, 1970 (unix time format)

player_name.description: Search matches with a player name, exact match only

hero_id.description: Search for matches with a specific hero being played, hero id's are in dota/scripts/npc/npc_heroes.txt in your Dota install directory

skill.description: 0 for any, 1 for normal, 2 for high, 3 for very high skill

date_max.description: date in UTC seconds since Jan 1, 1970 (unix time format)

account_id.description: Steam account id (this is not SteamID, its only the account number portion)

start_at_match_id.description: Start the search at the indicated match id, descending
